<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAPIST GETS 159 YEARS FOR ATTACKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An ex-felon convicted of sexually assaulting six women and one man was 
sentenced today to more than 159 years in state prison. 
</P>
<P>
 Calling Monette Johnson of Lake View Terrace a "menace to society," Superior 
Court Judge John Fisher sentenced him to the maximum term for the crimes he 
committed during a roughly seven-month spree. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnson, 35, was convicted last month of eight counts of rape and five other 
counts. 
</P>
<P>
 A seven-man, five-woman jury also found him guilty of six counts each of 
robbery and burglary, and a single charge of receiving stolen property. The 
panel deliberated less than two days.  
</P>
<P>
 "He should be taken off the streets and never set free again," Deputy Dist. 
Atty. Phillip Rabichow said. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnson will be eligible for parole in 79 years and eight months, Rabichow 
said.  
</P>
<P>
 The prosecutor said Johnson stalked his victims before breaking into their San 
Fernando Valley-area homes and sexually assaulting and robbing them. The 
attacks occurred between July, 1991, and his arrest on Jan. 9, 1992.  
</P>
<P>
 Johnson, who has a lengthy rap sheet, had been released on parole after 
serving time for extortion before his first attack, Rabichow said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
