<HEADLINE>
<P>
NBA ROUNDUP; CELTICS GET MUGGED BY BOGUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dee Brown learned a lesson that other guards have known for 10 years: You 
can't turn your back on Muggsy Bogues. 
</P>
<P>
 Bogues made a key steal in the closing seconds of regulation, then scored four 
points in the final 40 seconds of overtime to rally the Charlotte Hornets to a 
107-101 victory over the Boston Celtics Monday night at Charlotte, N.C. 
</P>
<P>
 Hersey Hawkins converted Bogues' steal into a layup with 19.5 seconds left to 
force the overtime. 
</P>
<P>
 Bogues even warned Brown that he would lose the ball. 
</P>
<P>
 "I told him I was going to get it," Bogues said. "He peeked at the shot 
clock." 
</P>
<P>
 Detroit 108, Sacramento 102 -- Isiah Thomas scored 20 of his 22 points in the 
first half and Terry Mills had 20 points for the Pistons at Sacramento. 
</P>
<P>
 Detroit outscored the Kings, 35-25, in the fourth quarter. Joe Dumars, who had 
been averaging 32 points in his last four games, scored only 16, but his 
three-pointer with 44 seconds left gave the Pistons a 104-98 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Denver 116, San Antonio 88 -- Mahmoud Abdul Rauf scored a season-high 33 
points to lead the Nuggets to an easy victory over the Spurs at Denver. David 
Robinson had a season-low eight points. 
</P>
