<P>
NHL ROUNDUP; FLORIDA GOALIE VANBIESBROUCK NOTCHES A SATISFYING VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Florida goaltender John Vanbiesbrouck got his second victory in four tries 
against his former team, the New York Rangers, making 27 saves in the Panthers' 
2-1 victory Monday night at Miami. Vanbiesbrouck spent his first 11 seasons 
with the Rangers before being traded to Vancouver and subsequently being 
selected by the Florida Panthers in the expansion draft. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory moved the Panthers within one point of the eighth-place 
Philadelphia Flyers in the Eastern Conference. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'd be lying if I said it wasn't extra special," said Vanbiesbrouck, who made 
10 saves in the third period to protect the lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Montreal 5, Boston 4 -- Goaltender Patrick Roy stopped Glen Murray and Glen 
Wesley on breakaways, and that helped the Canadiens come from behind to beat 
the Bruins at Montreal. 
</P>
<P>
 The Canadiens, after trailing 3-0, scored five goals in less than 19 minutes 
beginning late in the second period. 
</P>
<P>
 Quebec 5, Chicago 1 -- Scott Young and Mats Sundin each scored one goal and 
added two assists at Quebec as the Nordiques snapped the Blackhawks' six-game 
unbeaten streak. 
