<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: SPECIAL TODAY: MEAT, MEAT AND MORE MEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nutrition experts encourage consumers to eat low-fat, healthful foods, but 
meat dishes remain the most popular choices on restaurant menus. 
</P>
<P>
 A survey of restaurateurs by Thomas Food Industry Register, a trade 
publication, found the favored entrees are meat and poultry, served 44% of the 
time. Pasta was second at 33%, followed by vegetarian dishes, 10%; fish, 9%, 
and salad, 4%. 
</P>
