<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROBERTI DESERVES A PAT ON THE BACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * State Sen. David Roberti deserves compliments for the tremendous efforts he 
has extended to El Proyecto del Barrio. 
</P>
<P>
 El Proyecto del Barrio is a nonprofit human-service organization that provides 
multiple services, including primary medical care at two clinics in Arleta and 
Pacoima.The Pacoima clinic was severely damaged and "yellow tagged" for limited 
entry as a result of the earthquake. This designation rendered the clinic 
unable to provide urgent and primary medical care in the direct aftermath of 
the disaster. 
</P>
<P>
 Although faced with the distractions of the impending recall election, Roberti 
was the first elected official to offer his services. He assisted us in 
securing food donations that allowed El Proyecto del Barrio to distribute food 
to more than 5,000 people. He arranged for the lease of modular units and is 
assisting us in securing the necessary permits to set up the modular units. He 
visited the site of our damaged clinic and pledged to assist us in our efforts 
to provide medical services. All this was done without any fanfare or press 
releases. 
</P>
<P>
 With the recall forces stating that he does not care about his district and 
the wrath he is subject to due to his position on gun control, Sen. Roberti is 
due for some positive words. 
</P>
<P>
 We could not have resumed the immediate provision of medical services without 
his help. 
</P>
<P>
 CORINNE SANCHEZ, ESQ. 
</P>
<P>
 President/CEO 
</P>
<P>
 El Proyecto del Barrio 
</P>
<P>
 Arleta 
</P>
