<HEADLINE>
<P>
THANKS TO ALL WHO HELPED AFTER DISASTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * On behalf of our daughter, Heather, and her husband, Tom Denning, who lived 
in the apartment complex next to the Northridge Meadows, which dramatically 
collapsed, we want to thank publicly the many good citizens who provided so 
much help and support after the Jan. 17 earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 The Northridge Methodist Church immediately made available an office for 
coordinating relief efforts and communications with tenants.Guiliano's 
Delicatessen, which had much damage, helped the nearby residents with phone 
service and refreshments. 
</P>
<P>
 Later, firemen from many stations in Los Angeles city and county brought out 
personal belongings by ladder and ropes. That was a great physical and 
emotional lift. City building and safety workers also helped. 
</P>
<P>
 Then, when all insurance requirements had been arranged, Mike Mc Philomy and 
other Cullen and Sons Demolition Co. employees were very helpful and 
cooperative with tenants in bringing out personal items of financial and 
emotional value. 
</P>
<P>
 The police and National Guard members who protected the severely damaged 
complex from looting are also to be greatly commended. 
</P>
<P>
 So let's thank and remember the good people who have helped our daughter and 
son-in-law, and so many others, to begin to recover from a most devastating 
tragedy. They performed a beautiful and caring public service. 
</P>
<P>
 NANCY and JOHN SELLS 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys 
</P>
