<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FACULTY ACTED LIKE CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * I was amused by the story about the faculty and students of Los Angeles 
Valley College condemning Mary Lee, the college president, for reopening the 
college as scheduled (Feb. 11). 
</P>
<P>
 One can expect the students to behave like the children they are.Missing 
school is a treat. But the faculty behaved like petulant adolescents. 
</P>
<P>
 The instructors wanted postponement of the opening because of responsibilities 
to family and friends. I wonder if they would have voted the same way if their 
considerable salaries were docked for the days they missed because of the 
earthquake, as happened to so many others not in the education business. 
</P>
<P>
 Congratulations to President Lee for making the right decision. In the time of 
turmoil, going to classes and being responsible for learning gave some 
structure and a touch of normalcy to the students' lives. Community college 
faculties always babble about "shared governance" but never about shared 
responsibility. 
</P>
<P>
 M. STEPHEN SHELDON 
</P>
<P>
 Studio City 
</P>
