COLLEGE BASKETBALL DAILY REPORT; ACROSS THE NATION; TCU FIRES IBA AFTER 7-20 
SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Texas Christian Coach Moe Iba was fired after compiling a 96-108 record in 
seven seasons with the Horned Frogs. 
</P>
<P>
 "Coach Iba's first years at TCU were encouraging," TCU Athletic Director Frank 
Windegger said in a statement. "But our expectations for the program no longer 
are being met." 
</P>
<P>
 TCU was 7-20 this season, 3-11 in the Southwest Conference. Last season, the 
Horned Frogs were 6-22 and 2-12. 
</P>
<P>
 Iba will be paid for the remaining two years on his contract. 
