<HEADLINE>
<P>
CS NORTHRIDGE SIGNS THREE FROM COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In an attempt to rebound from his first losing season in eight years as 
football coach at Cal State Northridge, Bob Burt is returning to his roots. 
</P>
<P>
 The former Cal State Fullerton defensive coordinator has signed three prep 
defensive players from Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 Jason Sweet, a 6-foot-4, 220-pound linebacker from Estancia High, signed 
during the weekend. Signing in the past week were Pete Silvey, a 6-3, 230-pound 
linebacker from Mater Dei, and Jeff Bodholdt, a 6-3, 255-pound defensive 
lineman from Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 The Matadors were 4-6 last season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Conrad Byars, boys' basketball coach at Anaheim High the last 10 years, was 
recently named coach at Western High School, said Jim Howell, Western's 
athletic director. 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim, 6-13 last season, was 63-159 under Byars, 35. 
</P>
<P>
 At Western, Byars replaces Matt Cavanaugh, whose record was 27-23 over two 
seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The coaches for the 29th Orange County All-Star basketball game, April 23 at 
Orange Coast College, were announced Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Gordon Billingsley of Fountain Valley will coach the boys' team for the South 
and Mike Murphy of Sonora will coach the North. 
</P>
<P>
 For the girls, Mary Mulligan of San Clemente will head the South and Mary 
Houser of Mater Dei will lead the North. The players will be announced March 
23. 
</P>
