BRIEFLY: AGRICULTURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 FDA Reschedules Meeting on Calgene's Tomato: The food and drug agency will 
meet with a subcommittee of its Food Advisory Committee on April 6-8 to discuss 
the process it has followed in reviewing Calgene's Flavr Savr brand tomato.The 
meeting was postponed from last Wednesday and Thursday. The tomato, designed 
for more flavor and a longer shelf life, is expected to be the first 
genetically engineered food to be marketed. The FDA said it expects a decision 
on the tomato itself soon. 
</P>
