</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: PETER LUND TO HEAD REINSTATED CBS DIVISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CBS Inc., after a hiatus of several years, has reformed its network division 
and named Peter Lund as president. 
</P>
<P>
 Lund, who had been executive vice president of CBS/Broadcast Group and 
president of CBS Marketing since 1990, will oversee sales, marketing, 
communications and affiliate relations, as well as the CBS TV stations and CBS 
Radio divisions. 
</P>
<P>
 The network division was disbanded several years ago under Chief Executive 
Laurence A. Tisch. But CBS Broadcast Group President Howard Stringer said the 
network division is being reinstated to prepare CBS for "more growth and 
leadership in the future." Lund continues to report to Stringer. 
</P>
<P>
 Sony Pictures Entertainment's Motion Picture Group has named Gary Schrager 
executive vice president. He will serve as the group's primary deal-making 
strategist. 
</P>
<P>
