<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Michael Arkush 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CRYSTAL BALL: We hate to mess up all the Valley office pools, but we now know 
the teams in the Final Four of the NCAA tournament that begins Thursday. We got 
the scoop from CSUN Coach Pete Cassidy, whose team (8-18), believe it or not, 
didn't make it. . . . His picks: North Carolina, Purdue, Arkansas and 
Louisville. The winner: North Carolina. "I like their size and experience," he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 WRONG LARRY: We also asked Larry Bird. No, not that Larry Bird. This Bird, 46, 
is running for City Council in Santa Clarita. But he couldn't help us because 
he doesn't keep track of college basketball. He owns and manages an apartment 
building in Newhall and sometimes gets tired of being associated with the 
former Boston Celtic superstar. . . . "I had the name first." 
</P>
<P>
 MIGHTY MAGS: Big companies like to branch out -- that's why they're big 
companies. Disney is no exception. These days, the folks in Burbank (above) are 
putting a lot of effort into magazines. It's another way to get the Disney name 
out there. . . . The latest publication is a computer magazine for the whole 
family -- Family PC. See Valley Business, Page 12. 
</P>
<P>
 CHEAPER COMMUTE: Good news for some Metrolink riders: Starting April 1, the 
price of monthly passes is going down. For passengers from Antelope Valley, 
passes will go from $208 a month to either $112 or $80, depending on the final 
destination. Those commuters originating in Santa Clarita will also get better 
monthly deals. . . . The new fares will be in effect for three months. (B14) 
</P>
<P>
 MASTER'S MADNESS: OK, so it's not the big dance, but it's better than staying 
home. The Master's College in Newhall will play today in the first round of the 
NAIA Division I basketball tournament. . . . Master's faces a school that 
graduated a president. That's Georgia Southwestern, with Jimmy Carter and wife, 
Rosalyn, among its alumni. (C7) Michael Arkush 
</P>
</TEXT>
