<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: PLACENTIA; POLICE HOPE PHOTO WILL LEAD TO KILLER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TERRY SPENCER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The family of a slain Cal State Fullerton honor student and police released a 
photograph of the young woman's car Monday, hoping somebody will remember 
something that will help catch her killer. 
</P>
<P>
 Cathy Torrez, 20, was driving her red 1990 Toyota Corolla on Feb. 12 when she 
disappeared after leaving her job at the Sav-on Drug Store at Yorba Linda 
Boulevard and Bradford Avenue at 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Her body was found Feb. 19 in the trunk of the car in the front parking lot of 
the Placentia-Linda Medical Building.She had been stabbed. The building is part 
of the Placentia-Linda Community Hospital complex at 1301 N. Rose Drive. A 
doctor told police the car had been parked in the lot since at least Feb. 14. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have some leads, but we are still missing some pieces of the puzzle," 
Detective Donna Rose said. "Maybe somebody was taking their kid to the 
emergency room and saw something and this picture will help them remember." 
</P>
<P>
 Mary Bennett, Torrez's mother, said she hopes the crime will be solved soon. 
</P>
<P>
 "We need to know what happened," she said. "We need justice." 
</P>
<P>
 Sav-on, the city of Placentia and the union of which Torrez was a member have 
combined to donate $30,000 for information leading to the arrest and conviction 
of her killer. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives can be reached at (714) 993-8146 or (714) 993-8164. A 24-hour 
anonymous tip line is also available at (714) 993-8226. TERRY SPENCER 
</P>
