<HEADLINE>
<P>
POOR MANAGEMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It appears that the Ventura County Sheriff's Department is attempting to cover 
up poor management practices by punishing a pilot involved in the loss of a 
firefighting helicopter while being directed to use it to start a controlled 
burn. 
</P>
<P>
 If the department's chain of command functions with the lowest level employee 
bearing the ultimate responsibility and risk for the mistakes of those in 
charge, perhaps the grand jury should investigate the sheriff's management 
policies. 
</P>
<P>
 COLLETTE JONES 
</P>
<P>
 Camarillo 
</P>
