<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 MEN SHOT AT PARTY STILL HOSPITALIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two men shot at a party in El Rio over the weekend remained hospitalized 
Monday, one in serious condition, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Victor Carrillo, 22, of Santa Paula was in the intensive care unit of St. 
John's Regional Medical Center in Oxnard, a spokeswoman said.Sergio Martinez, 
19, of Oxnard was listed in good condition at the same hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Both were shot about 11 p.m. Saturday during a birthday party in the 1000 
block of Salem Avenue. According to the Sheriff's Department, two men in a 
heated argument were wrestling over a semiautomatic handgun when shots were 
fired into a crowd, wounding Carrillo and Martinez. 
</P>
<P>
 "There was a verbal argument and some shoving and then this thing occurred," 
Sheriff's Detective Raul Munoz said. 
</P>
<P>
 When deputies arrived, most of the people at the party had scattered, Munoz 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators are trying to identify the two men who had the gun. No arrests 
had been made by late Monday. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
