<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE REPORT 3 ARMED ROBBERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police reported three armed robberies over the past three days, one of them 
leaving a Santa Ana man critically wounded. 
</P>
<P>
 The injured man, Jose Ramos, 28, was stabbed about 2 a.m. Monday near Newport 
Pier, according to Sgt. Andy Gonis.He was stabbed two to three times in the 
upper torso and taken to a hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 A 17-year-old juvenile and two men, all of Santa Ana, were arrested shortly 
after the stabbing. 
</P>
<P>
 The two adult suspects were identified as Sylvester Diaz, 20, and Jose 
Jimenez, 18. Both are being held in Newport Beach City Jail on suspicion of 
attempted murder and armed robbery, with bail set at $250,000 each, Gonis said. 
</P>
<P>
 About 7 p.m. Sunday, a 36-year-old Newport Beach man walking on the beach near 
G Street was approached by two men with guns, authorities said. The man was 
forced to his nearby parked car to get his wallet. He turned over cash to the 
men, who fled by car. 
</P>
<P>
 At 4:30 a.m. Saturday, a man making a withdrawal from a Wells Fargo ATM in the 
3200 block of Newport Boulevard was robbed at gunpoint by a man driving a faded 
red Datsun, Gonis said. 
</P>
<P>
 The three robberies do not appear to be related, Gonis said. 
</P>
