<P>
 Home Sales Rise Again: Nearly 13,000 units were sold in the six-county 
Southern California area last month, up 7.5% from January and 26.4% higher than 
a year earlier, Dataquick Information Systems said.It was the eighth straight 
month in which sales showed a year-over-year gain. Month-to-month sales climbed 
14.5% in Los Angeles County, despite the lingering effects of the January 
earthquake, and surged 65% in Orange County. Prices were flat or slightly 
higher than a year ago in San Diego, Riverside and Ventura counties. Prices 
were down about 3% from year-earlier levels in Orange and Los Angeles counties, 
but the research firm said that the worst of the prolonged drop in prices 
appears to be over. 
