<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: TECHNOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Dean Takahashi, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 O.C.'s High-Tech Rebound: Orange County's high-tech industry may be on the 
rebound.A survey of local technology companies with fewer than 1,000 employees 
showed employment grew 6% through February compared to the same time a year 
ago. 
</P>
<P>
 Among national companies, employment grew only 4.6% for the same time period. 
The survey of 126 companies shows that employment grew at 38 of the companies. 
Hiring was flat at 88 companies and none reported layoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 The Orange County index has been up since October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
