<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: WASHINGTON; VISIT FROM IRELAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Irish Prime Minister Albert Reynolds visits Washington this week, and will 
call on President Clinton on Thursday, St. Patrick's Day, at the White House 
for a dinner honoring Irish culture in the United States. 
</P>
<P>
 An Administration official said Clinton plans to assure Reynolds of U.S. 
support for the Ireland-Britain peace plan for Northern Ireland. 
</P>
<P>
 "President Clinton has made it clear that he is willing to help in any way 
possible to combat the violence between the IRA and the Unionists in Northern 
Ireland," the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
