</P>
<P>
 Improving Populations 
</P>
<P>
 Migratory waterfowl in the Pacific Flyway have reached their most encouraging 
numbers in years, according to an annual mid-winter survey conducted last 
month. Most species, however, still have a long way to go to reach the healthy 
populations of decades ago. Every January, migratory birds -- mostly ducks, 
geese, swans and coots -- are counted by federal and state biologists in 
aircraft and on the ground. 05,07,11,11,11,11 1955-1992 1994 1992 1985 Average 
