REGIONAL EARNINGS: LESLIE'S POOLMART LOSES $1.88 MILLION IN 4TH QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Leslie's Poolmart, a Chatsworth-based retailer of swimming pool supplies, said 
its loss widened to $1.88 million in the fourth quarter, compared with the 
$1.73 million the company lost in the same period in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 Sales in the quarter that ended Dec. 31 grew 15% to $13.5 million, from $11.7 
million a year earlier. The company attributed the sales gain to changes in its 
marketing, merchandising and purchasing strategies, which also resulted in 
higher expenses. 
</P>
<P>
 For all of 1993, Leslie's posted a profit of $3.04 million, up 41% from a 
profit of $2.15 million in 1992. Sales last year increased 25% to $120 million, 
from $96.3 million in 1992. 
