<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: ARCS MORTGAGE OFFERS FHA QUAKE-DAMAGE LOANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ARCS Mortgage Inc., a Calabasas mortgage lender, said it is offering Federal 
Housing Administration mortgage loans to owners and renters of uninhabitable 
earthquake-damaged properties in Los Angeles, Ventura and Orange counties. 
</P>
<P>
 The loans have the new higher limits and flexible qualifying guidelines of the 
FHA's Earthquake Loan Program, which is administered by the federal Department 
of Housing and Urban Development. The program temporarily raises loan limits to 
$203,150 until Dec. 17, and offers 100% new financing and low interest rates. 
</P>
<P>
 ARCS is a subsidiary of the Bank of New York Co. 
</P>
